
// This Hyperlambda code logs an error message when a database creation process fails. It uses the [log.error] slot to log the error, capturing details such as the database name from [database], the script used from [script], and the error message from [error]. The [database] and [script] slots retrieve their values from the arguments, providing context for the error log.
log.error:Something went wrong when creating database
   database:x:@.arguments/@.arguments/*/database
   script:x:@.create-database-script
   error:x:@.arguments/*/message
